column2: # histCatchFD = Collect historical catch data? 1=yes, 2=no.
# histEffortFD = Collect historical catch data? 1=yes, 2=no.
# histStartYr = time step in which historical data was first collected
# Aggregate = Aggregate data over space? 1 for yes, 2 for no.
# SampStartYr = time step in which current sampling program begins
# SampFreq = Sampling Frequency
# sigHistCatch = Standard deviation of observation error on total catches. If no error, sigHistCatch=0.
# catchBias = Bias in catch reporting. Scalar between (-1, 1). 0 equals no bias.
# Sel50FI = Survey selectivity at age
# Sel95FI = Survey selectivity at age
# Sel50VB = Selectivity for von Bertlanffy surveys (usually uniform above a specific age)
# Sel95VB = Selectivity for von Bertlanffy surveys (usually uniform above a specific age)
# SurveyF = Fishing rate associated with survey effort
# nAgeFD = Number of fishery dependent age samples collected from each patch
# nAgeFI = Number of fishery independent age samples collected from each patch
# nSizeFD = Number of fishery dependent size samples collected from each patch
# nSizeFI = Number of fishery independent size samples collected from each patch
# numVB = Number of VB age-size samples collected from each patch
# VBbins = Size bins associated with von Bertalanffy survey
# lengthObsSD_FI = Observation Error on fishery independent lengths
# lengthObsSD_FD = Observation Error on fishery dependent lengths
# AgeObsSD_FI = Observation Error on fishery independent ages
# AgeObsSD_FD = Observation Error on fishery dependent ages

# FISurvType= Spatial pattern for fishery independent surveys (0 = input a .csv file specifying custom survey distribution, 1 = sample all patches, 2=sample no patches, 3 = sample random 20% of patches, 4= sample near and far site, 5=sample MPAs)

# FDSurvType = Spatial pattern for fishery dependent surveys (0 = input a .csv file specifying custom survey distribution, 1 = sample all fished patches, 2=sample no patches, 3 = sample random 20% of patches, 4= sample near and far site)
# Catch_FD = Collect fishery dependent catch data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Catch_FI = Collect fishery independent catch data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Effort_FI = Collect fishery independent abundance index data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Effort_FD = Collect fishery dependent CPUE data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Ages_FD = Collect fishery dependent age composition data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Ages_FI = Collect fishery independent age composition data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Sizes_FD = Collect fishery dependent size composition data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Sizes_FI = Collect fishery independent size composition data? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# VBSurvey = Collect age and size data to estimate VB params? 1 = yes, 2 = no.
# Survey_q = Survey catchability. Might be different depending on mode of survey (such as dive surveys)
# sigSurvey = Standard deviation of observation error on total catches. If no error, sigHistCatch=0.
